<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 03 at 6:19PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Stewart
County through 645 PM EDT...
At 619 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was centered near Sanford, or
10 miles southwest of Lumpkin. This storm was nearly stationary.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Lumpkin, Sanford and Providence Canyon State Park.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
